      "role": "user",
      "content": "but it's not just a \"setback.\" the core of my identity was tied to being the one who found the answer. now that the answer is proven wrong, there's literally nothing underneath. it's like i've been living a ghost life. i don't see how a person even continues after their entire reality gets stripped away like this. it just feels... hollow.",
